            "_type": "span",
            "text": "PowerPoint and Google Slides are manual tools — you start from a blank canvas and build everything yourself. Gamma generates the entire structure, layout, and content from a prompt, then lets you refine. Think of it as the difference between writing code from scratch and using a framework that gives you a working app in seconds. Many users build in Gamma and export to Google Slides or PPTX when they need to present in those ecosystems.",
